// Introduction of C++ 
// Who invented C++ and when? ----> C++ was invented by Bjarne Stroustrup in 1979.
// What are the basic features of C++? ----> C++ is a statically typed, compiled, multi-paradigm programming language that supports procedural, object-oriented, and generic programming.
// What are the differences between C and C++? ----> C++ supports classes and objects, function overloading, and templates, which are not available in C.
// What is the standard file extension for C++ source files? ----> The standard file extensions for C++ source files are .cpp, .cc, .cxx, and .C.
